Nintendo have published new content guidelines for online video and image sharing:
 &ldquo;We are humbled every day by your loyalty and passion for Nintendo&rsquo;s games, characters and worlds, and respect that you want to be able to express yourself creatively by sharing your own original videos and images using content from our games.&rdquo;
&ldquo;As long as you follow some basic rules, we will not object to your use of gameplay footage and/or screenshots captured from games for which Nintendo owns the copyright (&ldquo;Nintendo Game Content&rdquo;) in the content you create for appropriate video and image sharing sites.

Valve has appeared to have completely discontinued the Steam Link. On the official store page, Valve states that:
 &ldquo;The supply of physical Steam Link hardware devices is sold out. Moving forward, Valve intends to continue supporting the existing Steam Link hardware as well as distribution of the software versions of Steam Link, available for many leading smart phones, tablets and televisions.&rdquo;
